{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[garleac|gārlēac]], from [[gar#Old English|gār]] ‘spear’ (in reference to the cloves) + [[leac|lēac]] ‘leek’.

===Pronunciation===
*[[AHD]]: gärˈlĭk
*[[IPA]]: /ˈɡaɹ.lɪk/
*[[SAMPA]]: /'gA:(r)lIk/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑː(r)lɪk|-ɑː(r)lɪk]]

===Noun===
'''garlic''' ([[uncountable]], [[countable]])
# a plant related to the [[onion]].
# the bulbous [[root]] of the garlic plant, used to flavor [[food]].

====Scientific names====
*[[Allium sativum]]

